## Local run (30 seconds)

```bash
npm install
npm run db:push      # Prisma pushes schema to ~/.preview-forge/%%PF_PROJECT_NAME%%/dev.db
npm run dev          # Next.js on http://localhost:3000
```

Zero Docker. Zero Postgres. Zero environment setup beyond Node 20+.

## Stack

| Layer | Technology | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Frontend | Next.js 16 App Router | React Server Components |
| Backend | Next.js Route Handlers (or nestia if REST-first surface detected) | Type-safe |
| DB | SQLite (file: `~/.preview-forge/%%PF_PROJECT_NAME%%/dev.db`) | Outside repo tree (security) |
| ORM | Prisma (sqlite provider) | Enum / JSONB rejected by schema-lint for portability |
| Runtime | Node 20 LTS | No container |

## Graduation path (standard → pro → max)

When you're ready to deploy or need Postgres features:

```bash
# From project root, run:
bash scripts/graduate.sh pro        # adds Dockerfile, compose.yml, Postgres datasource
bash scripts/graduate.sh max        # adds full CI/CD + k8s manifests (v2+)
```

`graduate.sh` is **additive** — it only writes container/CI artifacts,
keeps your existing code untouched (devops-architect CP-1).

Or, in Claude Code:

```
/pf:new "%%PF_IDEA%%" --profile=pro      # regenerate with pro from scratch
```

## What's NOT here (by design)

- ❌ `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`, `.dockerignore`
- ❌ Postgres / Redis / message queues
- ❌ Multi-stage CI/CD (see `--profile=max`)
- ❌ Enum / JSONB Prisma columns (rejected by schema-lint)

## Safety notes

- `dev.db` files are `.gitignore`d. Never commit binary SQLite files.
- WAL sidecar files (`dev.db-wal`, `dev.db-shm`) are also ignored.
- Schema changes: `npm run db:push` for dev, `npm run db:migrate:dev` once
  you've added migration history (recommended before graduating).

